Road Accident Dashboard & Analysis
ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project is a data-driven dashboard and analysis tool built entirely in Microsoft Excel to visualize and analyze road accident data. The dashboard provides insights into accident trends, casualties, vehicle types involved, road conditions, and geographical distribution of incidents.

The purpose of this project is to demonstrate skills in:

Data Cleaning & Preparation

Interactive Dashboard Creation in Excel

Data Analysis & Visualization

Business Intelligence and Storytelling with Data

ðŸ“Š Key Features

Road Accident Dashboard

Total, slight, serious, and fatal casualties.

Casualties categorized by vehicle type, road surface, road map, location, and light condition.

Year-over-Year monthly comparison trends.

Interactive filter panels (Urban/Rural).

Road Accident Analysis Report

Total accidents, casualties, and fatalities with percentage changes.

Breakdown by urban vs. rural areas.

Casualties by road type (single, dual, motorway, slip road).

Day vs. Night accident distribution.

Geographic map visualization of accident locations.

ðŸ›  Tools & Skills Used

Microsoft Excel

Pivot Tables & Pivot Charts

Power Query (for data cleaning & transformation)

Conditional Formatting

Slicers & Interactive Filters

Advanced Formulas

Data Visualization & Storytelling

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)


ðŸš€ Insights from the Dashboard

Cars account for the majority of accidents (~79%).

Most casualties occur under slight injury category (~84%).

Urban areas see higher accident numbers compared to rural.

Night-time accidents are fewer but often more severe.

Seasonal/monthly trends indicate fluctuations in accident frequency.
